## 5. Strengths

| # | Area | Details |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | **Intelligent Multi-Phase Pipeline** | The 4-phase approach (extraction → code gen → execution → interpretation) is architecturally excellent. Instead of asking the LLM to analyze raw data (expensive and inaccurate), it generates executable pandas code, runs it in a sandbox, then has Gemini interpret computed results. This produces more accurate analyses at lower token cost. |
| 2 | **Sandbox Security (Defense-in-Depth)** | `code_executor.py` implements 4 layers: AST-based static analysis via `_SafetyVisitor`, blocked builtins/imports whitelist, subprocess isolation, and a 60-second timeout. This is a well-thought-out defense-in-depth model against LLM-generated malicious code. |
| 3 | **Smart Data Profiling** | `data_service.py` auto-detects dataset types (survey, time series, transactional, geographic, etc.) and generates domain-specific analysis suggestions. This provides the LLM with richer context, significantly improving output quality compared to generic prompts. |
| 4 | **Token-Efficient Context Building** | Schema context is dynamically sized with a `max_tokens` budget. Correlations are computed locally, only metadata (not raw data) is sent to the LLM. The extraction phase pulls out unique categorical values so the code generator knows exact column names — prevents hallucinated column references. |
| 5 | **Graceful Degradation** | Code execution has 2 retry attempts with error feedback to Gemini, plus a text-only fallback (Phase 3). If code fails completely, users still get useful analysis. Cached results show a "⚡ Cached" badge for transparency. |
| 6 | **UX Polish** | Progress phases during AI processing, follow-up suggestion chips, chart annotations (click to label), drag-and-drop dashboard with column spanning, fullscreen chart expansion, data preview side panel — high attention to user experience for a prototype. |
| 7 | **Clean Modular CSS** | Stylesheets are split into 4 concerns: layout, chat, grid, overlays. Imported via a manifest (`dashboard.css`). CSS variables used for theming. Good organization. |
| 8 | **All Dependencies Pinned** | `requirements.txt` pins exact versions for all 7 packages — excellent for reproducibility and security. |
| 9 | **Easy Launch** | `start.bat` handles Python checks, dependency installation, server start, and browser launch in one click — low friction for non-technical users. |
| 10 | **Query Caching** | LRU cache (300 items) with MD5 hash keys prevents redundant API calls for repeated questions, saving both time and API costs. |

