## 6. Weaknesses

### 6.1 Critical Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **No Authentication (Fixed)** | `login.html` now uses Supabase Auth with real signup/login. JWT tokens stored in localStorage. All API endpoints protected by `@require_auth` decorator. | `login.html`, `auth_service.py`, `server.py` |
| 2 | **Single-User Global State (Fixed)** | `AppState` replaced with `SessionManager` — per-user `UserState` keyed by `user_id` from JWT. Thread-safe with `threading.Lock`. | `app_state.py` |
| 3 | **Thread Safety Missing (Fixed)** | `QueryCache` and `SessionManager` now use `threading.Lock()` for all state access and mutations. | `app_state.py` |
| 4 | **No Persistent Storage (Fixed)** | Supabase PostgreSQL database created with `profiles`, `chat_sessions`, `dashboard_configs` tables. RLS enabled. Per-user upload directories. | `server.py`, Supabase |
| 5 | **File Cache Unbounded** | `_file_cache` in `AppState` has no eviction policy — grows indefinitely with each new file upload. On a long-running server, this causes OOM. | `app_state.py` |

### 6.2 Security Concerns

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **No Rate Limiting** | Chat and suggestion endpoints trigger expensive LLM calls. No throttling means easy API abuse/DOS. | `server.py` |
| 2 | **No Prompt Injection Protection** | User questions are interpolated directly into LLM prompts. A crafted question could manipulate the system prompt, causing unintended code generation. | `gemini_service.py` |
| 3 | **Sandbox Escape Risk** | While AST validation blocks known dangerous patterns, `__subclasses__()` chains and metaclass tricks are not fully blocked. A sufficiently crafted payload could potentially escape. | `code_executor.py` |
| 4 | **No HTTPS (Fixed)** | Flask server now supports HTTPS with self-signed certificates via `HTTPS_ENABLED=true` in `.env`. Auto-generates certs in `certs/` directory. | `server.py`, `app_config.py` |
| 5 | **CDN Dependencies Without SRI** | 6 external libraries loaded from CDN without Subresource Integrity hashes. A compromised CDN could inject malicious code. | `dashboard.html` |
| 6 | **Path Traversal Incomplete** | File path validation exists but `.` resolution not fully enforced in all paths. | `server.py` |
| 7 | **No CORS Validation** | Malformed origins from env var accepted without validation. | `app_config.py` |

### 6.3 Performance Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **DataFrame Copied Per Execution** | Full DataFrame is copied for every code execution call — doubles memory for large files. | `code_executor.py` |
| 2 | **O(n²) Correlation Computation** | Numeric correlation matrix computed for all column pairs — slow/expensive with 100+ columns. | `data_service.py` |
| 3 | **Subprocess Per Query** | A new Python process is spawned for every single chat query. Process creation overhead adds 0.5-1s per request. | `code_executor.py` |
| 4 | **No File Size Validation Client-Side** | Users can attempt uploading 1GB files with no client-side warning — only server validates after full upload. | `js/core.js` |
| 5 | **Particle Animation O(n²) (Fixed)** | `connectParticles` computes distance for *every* pair every frame. Very heavy on CPU. Needs spatial partitioning or bounding boxes. | `js/core.js` |

### 6.4 Code Quality Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **Zero Test Coverage** | No unit tests, integration tests, or end-to-end tests for any component. The sandbox, data parsing, and API endpoints are all untested. | Entire project |
| 2 | **Silent Failures** | `gemini_service` returns `None` instead of raising exceptions. Backend errors are swallowed with `console.error()` on frontend — users don't know what failed. | `gemini_service.py`, all JS |
| 3 | **Magic Numbers Everywhere (Fixed)** | History caps (5, 6 messages), timeouts (60s), token budgets, chart heights (340px, 380px, 420px), animation delays (100ms, 350ms, 2500ms) scattered with no documentation. | All files |
| 4 | **Hardcoded `API_BASE` (Fixed)** | Now uses `window.location.origin`. Works in any deployment. | `js/core.js` |
| 5 | **Hardcoded User Identity (Fixed)** | User profile now dynamically populated from Supabase Auth session. | `dashboard.html`, `js/core.js` |
| 6 | **No JSDoc / Docstrings** | Frontend functions have no documentation. Backend has minimal docstrings. Unclear parameter expectations. | All files |
| 7 | **Inconsistent Error Handling** | `pinChart()` uses `alert()`, `refreshDashboard()` swallows errors silently, some endpoints return different error shapes. | `js/dashboard-ui.js`, `server.py` |
| 8 | **Large Monolithic `chat()` Function** | The main chat endpoint handler is 144 lines — should be decomposed into pipeline stages. | `server.py` |

### 6.5 UX / Accessibility Issues

| # | Area | Details |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | **No Responsive Design** | Sidebar is fixed 260px, dashboard grid is fixed 3-column, no tablet/mobile breakpoints except a single 768px query in `styles.css`. App is unusable on mobile. |
| 2 | **No Keyboard Navigation** | Drag-and-drop has no keyboard alternative. No focus traps in modals. No skip links. Chat send button requires mouse. |
| 3 | **SVG Icons Without Labels (Fixed)** | Navigation icons have no `aria-label`. Screen readers cannot identify sidebar sections. |
| 4 | **No Focus Management (Fixed)** | Fullscreen chart modal has no `aria-modal`, no focus trap, can't be closed with Escape key. |
| 5 | **Color-Only Indicators (Fixed)** | Active nav item, cached badge, and error states rely on color alone — fails WCAG 2.1 SC 1.4.1. |
| 6 | **No Debounce on Chat Send (Fixed)** | Users can spam the send button, creating multiple concurrent API requests. |
| 7 | **Typing Indicator Timing Mismatch (Fixed)** | Progress phases rotate on a fixed 2.5s timer regardless of actual API response time — misleading. |
| 8 | **Landing Page Links Broken** | Navigation links (Products, Solutions, etc.) and CTA buttons on `index.html` all point to `#`. |
| 9 | **Upload Success Shows Before Data Loads (Fixed)** | Success banner appears before grid is populated — user sees "success" with empty grid. |

